  "text": "The Jak-STAT signaling is essential for the induction of milk protein expression in mammary tissue of non-ruminants, but in ruminants and particularly in the bovine, expression of milk proteins appears to require a basic activity of this pathway but is not directly modulated by the change in expression of Jak and/or Stat genes, rather, it seems to be modulated by down-stream effectors of the pathway (e.g., ELF5) [CITATION_1] .",
